courses.learning_outcomes:
Upon completion of this course, students will be able to:

1. thoroughly understand the basic concepts of dictionary making;
2. systematically distinguish the structure, features, and functions of dictionaries;
3. critically compare and evaluate different dictionaries;
4. competently use dictionaries to solve various problems in translation, demonstrating effective analytical reasoning, critical thinking, and problem solving skills.

Upon completion of the course, students learn to:

1. have a general understanding of the Chinese and Western translation traditions;
2. critically analyze the common translation practices in different periods through history, including translation method, translation policy, source-text selection and target-text reception;
3. develop critical awareness and appreciation of the contribution of outstanding translators in China and the West;
4. be sensitive to the relationship between translation and ideology, and the relationship between translation movements and social, literary, cultural and political movements in history; and

5. develop an independent objective perspective on translation issues and historical incidents.

1. To understand principles and process of simultaneous interpreting between Putonghua and English;
