2. Basic strategies for subtitling: C-E and E-C;
3. Translating culture-specific items;
4. Translating humour and slang;
5. Translating different film genres: drama, comedy, action/martial arts; documentary;
6. Some theoretical perspectives.

courses.learning_outcomes:
Upon completion of the course, students learn to:

1. rationalize and handle issues involved in financial translation;
2. acquire a basic understanding of the operation of financial markets and institutions;
3. develop critical writing skills and translation strategies for different types of financial texts for different purposes;
4. analyze critically and express communicatively the discourse characteristics and reference network of different source texts and target texts, including their own translations;
5. acquire keys concepts and terminology in the financial field;
6. develop critical understanding of financial news and world issues;
7. utilize various reference tools for translation and background research; and

